        "rich_text_GJ8ieW": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Understanding The Basics of Ring Sizes ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Understanding The Basics of Ring Sizes </h2><p>Before you measure your ring size, it helps to understand what a <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/all-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Rings\">ring </a>size is. A ring size is the inner diameter or the circumference of the ring; it reflects how wide the ring should be to sit well on your finger. Different countries use different measuring systems such as some countries follow a ring size chart in cm. For example, India uses a scale between 6-30, while the European system uses millimetre based numbers, and the UK and Australia have an alphabetical system. When shopping from a global brand, knowing this helps because even the tiniest difference in millimetres can decide if the ring is of the right size or not. Precision in ring size is critical, which is why a conversion chart helps.</p>",
            "custom_id": "basics",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_4Kr8mz": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "International Size Conversion Guide",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>International Size Conversion Guide</h2>",
            "custom_id": "conversion",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_W74HCY": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image with Text- Save yourself",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Size_chart_8fdd8354-57ec-4d8f-9f66-5a508d375e2a.png",
            "text": "<p>Save yourself from sizing surprises with this international size chart. When buying jewelry from global brands online, you need not worry about whether it is the correct size if you’ve this ring measurement chart. We are happy to customise the ring as per any metric. Our expert consultants would be happy to guide you to measure your ring size, whether your ring travels to Mumbai, Canada, New York, Dubai, or any part of the world. No matter where you shop from, we want your ring fit to feel flawless..</p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": false,
            "products": []
          }
        },
        "rich_text_6q6way": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "How to Measure Your Ring Size at Home",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>How to Measure Your Ring Size at Home</h2><p>Now that the conversion chart is handy, you can easily measure the ring size at home without a ring sizer or any special equipment. With a few easy steps and convenient methods, you can know your ring size from the comfort of your home.</p>",
            "custom_id": "measure",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_ryQMtC": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The String or Paper Strip Method",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>The String or Paper Strip Method</h3>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_3GrC9r": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image with text-To measure your ring size at home",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/String_Method_88151c43-d59e-44c9-a8ea-b4e4aa639e2e.png",
            "text": "<p>To measure your ring size at home, take a thin strip of paper or a piece of string and gently wrap it around the base of your finger. Mark the point where the ends meet and measure that length in millimeters using a ruler. Then, refer to our <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lucira Jewelry\">Lucira Jewelry</a> ring size chart to find the corresponding size. For best accuracy, it’s ideal to measure your finger in the evening, when it’s at its natural size. Warm hands tend to give more reliable results, so avoid measuring when your hands are cold, as fingers shrink slightly in lower temperatures. </p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": false,
            "products": []
          }
        },
        "rich_text_88nmJi": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "To measure your ring size at home-2",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p> It’s also best to avoid alcohol or salty foods before measuring, as they can cause temporary swelling. If your knuckle is larger than the base of your finger, measure both areas and choose a size in between. This ensures your ring will slide over the knuckle comfortably while still fitting snugly once worn.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_DMYqWB": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Measuring an Existing Ring",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Measuring an Existing Ring<br/><br/></h3>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_kxDgfi": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Already_own_ring.png",
            "text": "<p>If you already have a ring that fits the finger you plan to wear your new piece on, you can use it to find your size easily. This is the most preferred method to measure women's ring sizes. Begin by selecting that well-fitting ring—make sure it sits comfortably and doesn’t feel tight or loose. Next, take a flexible measuring tape (or a ruler if you don’t have one) and measure the inner diameter of the ring from one inner edge straight across to the opposite inner edge, ensuring you measure the widest point. </p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": false,
            "products": []
          }
        },
        "rich_text_czN389": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Once you have this measurement in millimeters",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Once you have this measurement in millimeters, simply refer to Lucira Jewelry’s ring size conversion chart to identify your corresponding size in Indian, US, or UK standards. This method is one of the most reliable for at-home measurement, especially if the ring you’re using already feels perfect on your chosen finger.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_d3GN8T": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Ring Sizer Mobile Applications ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Ring Sizer Mobile Applications </h3>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_4bADB6": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Mobile_Application.png",
            "text": "<p>You may wonder if there’s any way to ‘measure my ring size online.’ You can find online ring sizer applications that help you measure your ring size. It is important to check their reliability, and it is best to double-check the results with a professional sizing in a jewelry boutique.</p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": false,
            "products": []
          }
        },
        "rich_text_cMPRTW": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Lucira Jewelry’s Recommended Methods for a Perfect Fit",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Lucira Jewelry’s Recommended Methods for a Perfect Fit</h3><p>While measuring the ring size at home can be done correctly, professional sizing ensures precision and eliminates any doubt. At<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\" Lucira Jewelry\"> Lucira Jewelry</a>, our rings are crafted to have a comfortable fit - a snug fit that is designed to wrap the curves of your finger. </p><h3>Virtual Guidance </h3><p>Our consultants can guide you to help you measure ring size correctly using our ring size chart or a ring of your own, ensuring that you can avoid some common mistakes our expert jewellery consultants know that happen while measuring the size at home.<br/><br/></p>",
            "custom_id": "lucira",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_wDPB9K": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "In-Store Consultation",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>In-Store Consultation<br/><br/></h2>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_BH3rf8": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/In-Store_Consultation.png",
            "text": "<p>Visit our store and get your finger measured with absolute accuracy. Every <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/all-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lucira Jewelry ring \">Lucira Jewelry ring </a>is crafted with meticulous precision that sits perfectly along the finger’s contour. Our ring sizer in-store quickly helps you know your ring sizes in mm. Moreover, you can have a look at which band size and ring design would suit you best according to your size. With customization options made easy for all mens ring sizes and women's ring sizes with Lucira Jewelry’s magnetic ring builder, you can easily do ring shopping without any hassle. </p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": false,
            "products": []
          }
        },
        "rich_text_QxGiGA": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Common Sizing Mistakes and How To Avoid Them",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Common Sizing Mistakes and How To Avoid Them</h2><p>Even a small measuring error can lead to either the ring getting too tight or it easily slipping off. Here are the few most common mistakes and how to avoid them:</p><h3>Using Inaccurate Charts </h3><p>Always use a trusted chart with international sizes for reliability and convenience. Charts can differ slightly from one brand to another. Lucira Jewelry’s international size chart is tried and trusted, with no room for error when done properly at home. </p><h3>Ignoring The Width Of The Band</h3><p>Wider bands have a more snug fit than thin ones. When choosing a thicker band, consider going half a size up. </p><h3>Measuring At The Wrong Time </h3><p>Don’t measure early in the morning or in cold temperatures, fingers are smaller then. </p><h3>Using The Wrong Ribbon Or Paper Or Not Holding It Correctly</h3><p>Many people use stretchy, thick, or crumpled paper or loosely hold the string, which leads to inaccurate measurements. Always use a thin, non-stretchable strip of paper or thread for accuracy. It is also important to snugly wrap it around the finger you intend to wear the ring on. The string or paper should sit firmly around your finger, without gaps, but not so tight that it squeezes the skin. </p>",
            "custom_id": "mistakes",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_K8bibV": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Conclusion - Finding Your Forever Fit ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Conclusion - Finding Your Forever Fit </h2><p>A ring should feel like a part of you, not just by design but also secured to feel like second skin, and effortlessly graceful. At <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lucira Jewelry\">Lucira Jewelry</a>, we craft jewelry to match precise measurements to maximize this very comfort that a ring must provide. Our designers consider factors like metal type, band thickness, and gemstone setting ensuring a balance between beauty and wearability. With DIY ring sizing hacks at home, it is easier than ever before to shop fine jewelry online. If you’re still unsure, let our jewelry experts assist you. After all, finding a forever fit is the first step to finding your forever piece.</p>",
            "custom_id": "conclusion",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        }
